10/07/2003
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- President Janez Drnovsek met on Wednesday (9 July) with his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Svetozar Marovic, who said his country has opened a new chapter in relations with Slovenia.Marovic also told reporters that Serbia-Montenegro wants to see the entire region admitted into the EU. 
The two leaders also discussed ways to strengthen economic co-operation.
In other news Wednesday, a delegation from Serbia-Montenegro was in Sarajevo to discuss military co-operation. 
The delegations exchanged views on defence reforms, participation in the Partnership for Peace programme and implementation of arms control agreements. 
(AFP, SRNA, BBC - 09/07/03)
